short_description: PyCon Italia is the national conference where professionals, researchers and enthusiasts of the most beautiful programming language gather.

PyCon Italia is the national conference where professionals, researchers and enthusiasts of the most beautiful programming language gather together. In the wonderful setting of Florence, PyCon is a weekend for learning, meeting and discovering.

Starting from this edition, PyCon Italy's structure will change: it will become a multi-thematic event featuring the most important subcommunities of the Python universe. Each subcommunity will have its own space in the conference, its thematic tracks, but also sprints, open-spaces and events. All this is free for the conference attendees.

PyCon Italia will be held near the old city centre of Florence, at the Grand Hotel Mediterraneo.

PyData Florence 2016 is going to be a three-days event (April, 15-17 2016), held in conjunction with PyCon Sette  the seventh edition of the Italian Python Conference. The conference venue is located nearby the old city centre of Florence, at the Grand Hotel Mediterraneo.

Following up from the overnight success of the last year, PyData Italy will be held again in Florence, and again during PyCon Sette the seventh edition of the PyCon Italia Conference. PyData Florence will provide a meeting place where data scientists and engineers could join efforts, aiming at establishing a strong Italian PyData community.

name: Startup Weekend Mega Centro (Vertical Fintech)
short_description: Startup Weekend are 54 - hour events designed to provide high - quality experiential education for tech & non-technical entrepreneurs.
description:
This vertical seeks to innovate in the processes of the financial sector; and promote financial inclusion. It is intended that participants of these projects use technological tools along with their expertise in the financial sector to influence the way the finances are made in Latin America and the world.

Startup Weekend are 54 - hour events designed to provide high - quality experiential education for technical and non - technical entrepreneurs. Friday begins in the afternoon with the presentation of business ideas and team, continuing brainstorming, developing a business model, creating a basic prototype and generating information to validate the existence of a business opportunity as well as the size of the opportunity. Startup Weekends ends on Sunday evening with final presentations and demonstrations of equipment. Participants learn to create startups during the event, taking the opportunity to collaborate with like - minded individuals in a simulated, risk - free environment. The teams will have access to lectures and feedback from experts in different disciplines and receive valuable feedback about their projects, entrepreneurs and experts from the local community. The weekend is focused on action, innovation and education. It may be that you're looking for feedback on your idea, develop specific skills, know a co-founder, form a team to help you run your project or just learn, Startup Weekend is the ideal place to try and make the first steps towards setting launch your own startup.

Covering all aspects of digital marketing, from search and social all the way through to content, programmatic, email, data and more, this year’s agenda has been formatted to relate directly to customer experience.

name: Digiday Video Anywhere Summit
short_description: Video is anywhere and anytime consumers want it to be. Publishers and media companies are responding with complex video business models .
description:
Video is anywhere and anytime consumers want it to be. Publishers and media companies are responding with complex video business models for this to take advantage of this new video audience and the expected increased flow of advertising dollars. From content quality, platform fragmentation, inconsistent measurement and monetization, it is extremely difficult to do well at a meaningful financial scale.
At the Digiday Video Anywhere Summit, hear from leading companies in publishing, media, advertising and technology on how they’re tackling these problems head-on and trying to find the big business they can see but not yet touch.

name: O'Reilly Software Architecture Conference
short_description: Software architecture is a massive multidisciplinary subject, covering many roles and responsibilities, which makes it challenging to teach.
description:
Software architecture is a massive multidisciplinary subject, covering many roles and responsibilities, which makes it challenging to teach because so much context is required for every subject. It's also a fast-moving discipline, where entire suites of best practices become obsolete overnight.

The O'Reilly Software Architecture Conference is designed to provide the necessary professional training that software architects and aspiring software architects need to succeed. A unique event, it covers the full scope of a software architect's job, from IT to leadership and business skills. It also provides a forum for networking and hearing what other professionals have learned in real-world experiences.

name: NYC Startup Job Fair Spring 2016
short_description: NYC Startup Job Fair 2016 connects top NYC-area talent with the best startups in New York. Registration is required @ NYC.StartupJobFair.org
registration_details: Exhibitors and Job Seekers Register Here
description:
The Startup Job Fair announced its NYC Startup Job Fair Spring event on Friday, April 8th in the IAC Building in lower Manhattan. The event runs from 12:00-2:00PM for developers only and 2:00-5:00PM for all job seekers. Registration is mandatory in advance for both exhibiting startups and job seekers, and both can register on NYC.StartupJobFair.org. There are also volunteer opportunities to get closer networking access to the top startups in the business through service. 

Since 2009, the Startup Job Fair has been running successfully for years providing NYC startups and job seekers a way to connect physically and solidify strong hires quickly. This year, the IAC Building will limit startup exhibitor capacity to just around 80 startups, and those spots are likely to fill up way before the event date, with a waiting list of startups lining up to set up a booth. Job seekers are expected in the thousands. Historically, the event brings more than 2,000 developers and non-developers looking for jobs by speaking to hiring managers in person.

While the NYC Startup Job Fair is the first event and the cornerstone of the company's reputation, StartupJobFair runs other events across North America, in Boston (April 5th), Toronto (April 28th), San Francisco (Fall 2016), and Chicago (April 21st). It is also planning on opening up new markets and partnerships in more cities. More information about other cities is detailed on StartupJobFair.org

name: PyData Madrid 2016
short_description: PyData conferences bring together users and developers of data analysis tools to share ideas and learn from each other.
venue_name: BBVA Innovation Center, Saint Bárbara Square
description:
PyData brings together users and developers of data analysis tools in Python and other languages. PyData conferences provide a crucial space for contributors to come together, share ideas, and learn from each other. The PyData community gathers to discuss how best to apply languages and tools to continuously evolving challenges in data management, processing, analytics, and visualization.

They aim to be an accessible, community-driven conference, with tutorials for novices, advanced topical workshops for practitioners, and opportunities for package developers and users to meet in person.

PyData provides a venue for users across all the various domains of data analysis to share their experiences and techniques. The conference is an opportunity to highlight the triumphs and potential pitfalls of using different languages for certain kinds of problems.

name: Startup Weekend São José do Rio Preto
short_description: Startup Weekend is a 54 hour event that aims to connect individuals to startups universe.
description: Startup Weekend is a 54 hour event that aims to connect individuals to startups universe More than create startup success, the real purpose of Startup Weekend is to create connections and offer on a weekend week intense "push" for digital entrepreneurship. How it works the event begins with the present business ideas and selection by voting, made ​​by the participants themselves. Popular options saw working groups formed by the person who proposed the idea and other participants who did not have enough votes. . From there begins the modeling of new business and the development of prototypes, and the idea begins to take shape in the hands of the participants Throughout the course participants have the support of mentors; a group of professionals with experience in entrepreneurship. With them, the groups draw business models, validate solutions, develop projects and initiate new projects. The third and final step is the presentation of ideas, as well as the awarding of the best entrepreneurship models. Under the eyes of some of the main investors in the country, entrepreneurs will have the opportunity to showcase their innovative design and secure a sponsorship to make it a reality!

name: Startup Weekend "Tourism Edition" Palermo
short_description: Startup Weekend Edition Tourism is a big workshop that brings together people with training and different experiences.
description:
The Startup Weekend Edition Tourism is a big workshop that brings together people with training and different experiences but united in the sharing of a dream, to realize a project.
The Startup Weekend, arrived in the city in its fifth edition. is an event lasting 54 hours (from Friday afternoon to Sunday evening) which brings together developers, designers, business and developer marketing, product managers, and in general all those who are interested in the world of web, mobile, IT and innovation in general.

This edition is dedicated to the vertical market of tourism and will take place, for the second time as part of Travelexpo, the International Exhibition of Tourism, whose eighteenth edition is scheduled in Palermo, at the renovated hall 20 former Fair Mediterranean, dubbed "Spazio.20 ideas in motion" .L'intento of this event is to promote a prolific encounter between those who have ideas, proposals and initiatives with all those who can and make them operational with those who can make a real company. For this reason, the Startup Weekend is not limited to bringing together ideas and developers but also already started entrepreneurship reality, always ready to give feedback and advice, and investors, always looking for interesting projects.

The mechanism underlying the Startup Weekend is very simple and addictive. On Friday all participants will have a few minutes available to put on the table their ideas. The most interesting ideas will participate in the "game". The various professionals (Developers, Product Managers, etc ..) will decide to join a project in the race thus forming real complete team. From Saturday morning to Sunday afternoon, the participants will be able to create the company also thanks to the assistance of the Mentor that will give a hand with advice and feedback "on the run". Sunday night you will see the fruits of the marathon. Among presentations and prototypes, the dreams of many will become reality ready to be evaluated by potential investors.

Startup Weekend and 'an event NON PROFIT: all funds are used for the welfare of the participants. The ticket price is to cover the costs of food, beverages, stationery etc, which will be offered to the participants of the event from start to finish. All other costs are incurred by local and national sponsors, sensitive to the topic of entrepreneurship and innovation.

The ideas are proposed by the participants themselves, who will vote the best 7 to work from 5 to 8 people in the team during the next two days. It is not necessary to come up with an idea. Those who do not show up with his idea likes to vote on questions and to get to choose the team they prefer. A jury will evaluate the three best ideas that will be supported in the development through the awards. Prizes will be aimed at supporting the further development of the 3 ideas.

name: WordCamp London 2016
short_description: WordCamp London is a community organised WordPress event running for the third year since 2013.
description:
WordCamp London is a community organised WordPress event running for the third year since 2013. It’s aimed at anybody who uses, builds or simply has an interest in WordPress; including bloggers, core developers and end-users. They warmly welcome all levels of experience from beginners through to professionals.

With three-tracks over two days, WordCamp London ensures there is ample opportunity for all WordPress lovers to come together to share knowledge and discuss ideas; as well as a third day where attendees can kindly volunteer their time to contribute back to the project, and meet with the other likeminded people who make WordPress incredible.

They’ll also host an official after-party for all the attendees, and on top of all this goodness you’ll take home some seriously cool London-inspired WordCamp swag.
